TY  - JOUR
AU  - Pancost, N Aaron
AU  - Robatto, Roberto
T1  - The Effects of Capital Requirements on Good and Bad Risk-Taking
PY  - 2023
Y1  - 2023/02/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhac037
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 36
IS  - 2
SP  - 733
EP  - 774
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - We study capital requirement regulation in a dynamic quantitative model in which nonfinancial firms, as well as households, hold deposits. A novel general equilibrium channel that operates through firms deposits mitigates the cost of increasing capital requirements. In the calibrated model, (a) the optimal capital requirement is 7.3 percentage points higher than in a comparable model in which all the deposits are held by households, and (b) setting the capital requirement higher than the true optimum is not as costly as one would gauge from the comparable model. We also provide some independent evidence that supports our novel channel.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhac037
ER  - 



